00:22:12,079 --> 00:22:13,599
isn't until the lunch hour.

533
00:22:14,240 --> 00:22:16,559
You sleep the better part of the morning away

534
00:22:16,559 --> 00:22:17,839
and are waking up.

535
00:22:17,839 --> 00:22:19,440
Sun's a little higher in the sky

536
00:22:19,440 --> 00:22:20,639
than had previously mentioned.

537
00:22:20,639 --> 00:22:22,000
Maybe you woke up a little bit

538
00:22:22,000 --> 00:22:23,440
and you just close your eyes again

539
00:22:23,440 --> 00:22:24,639
and then woke up at 1030.

540
00:22:25,440 --> 00:22:28,559
I'm going to put on the best clothes that I brought

541
00:22:28,559 --> 00:22:30,480
because it's the first day of school.

542
00:22:30,480 --> 00:22:31,279
Got to look sharp.

543
00:22:33,039 --> 00:22:35,279
And I'm going to head back over.

544
00:22:35,279 --> 00:22:38,879
I'm assuming Gabriel's back at the inn again

545
00:22:38,879 --> 00:22:40,720
or am I eating him somewhere else?

546
00:22:41,359 --> 00:22:44,240
I think he told you to meet him there

547
00:22:44,880 --> 00:22:46,799
at the Fallen Tower.

548
00:22:46,799 --> 00:22:47,359
Okay, yeah.

549
00:22:47,359 --> 00:22:50,559
So one final spot check in the mirror before I go

550
00:22:50,559 --> 00:22:53,519
and I make my way back to the Fallen Tower.

551
00:22:55,359 --> 00:22:56,720
You make your way back down

552
00:22:56,720 --> 00:23:00,559
and you pass by Shilso who calls to you

553
00:23:00,559 --> 00:23:02,000
and says, you found everything okay?

554
00:23:03,519 --> 00:23:04,240
Everything was great.

555
00:23:04,240 --> 00:23:06,720
The note and the key, it was all perfect.

556
00:23:06,720 --> 00:23:07,359
Ah, good.

557
00:23:07,359 --> 00:23:07,920
Yes, yes.

558
00:23:07,920 --> 00:23:08,960
Well, good.

559
00:23:08,960 --> 00:23:11,039
Well, you're off for your day then?

560
00:23:11,039 --> 00:23:15,200
Are you going to go do what people

561
00:23:15,200 --> 00:23:16,879
who don't go to this school but stay here do?

562
00:23:17,920 --> 00:23:21,519
Yeah, I'm going to go talk to this Gabriel guy

563
00:23:21,519 --> 00:23:23,759
and see if he can teach me a thing or two.

564
00:23:23,759 --> 00:23:24,960
And I had a question.

565
00:23:24,960 --> 00:23:27,920
Is there like a laundry service here at the school as well?

566
00:23:27,920 --> 00:23:29,920
Because I mean, I only brought a couple of outfits

567
00:23:29,920 --> 00:23:32,559
and one is pretty dirty after some travel.

568
00:23:32,559 --> 00:23:34,240
So I wonder if I can maybe get it cleaned.

569
00:23:35,200 --> 00:23:37,279
Yep, we could probably do that for you.

570
00:23:38,240 --> 00:23:39,039
You're staying here.

571
00:23:39,039 --> 00:23:43,359
We can just, if you just, you know, here's a bag.

572
00:23:44,319 --> 00:23:45,920
Just leave it outside your door.

573
00:23:45,920 --> 00:23:48,639
It'll be cleaned up for you by the time you get back.

574
00:23:48,639 --> 00:23:49,519
Oh, oh, perfect.

575
00:23:49,519 --> 00:23:50,240
That's awesome.

576
00:23:50,240 --> 00:23:53,680
So I run back to my room and throw those clothes in a bag.

577
00:23:56,399 --> 00:23:59,920
You head back out and down and out to the Fallen Tower

578
00:23:59,920 --> 00:24:02,319
unless you're stopping anywhere else on the way.

579
00:24:03,119 --> 00:24:05,359
No, I figured I'd probably go right there nice and early.

580
00:24:05,359 --> 00:24:06,960
You know, apt pupil, et cetera.

581
00:24:07,759 --> 00:24:11,920
You make it there, I'd say you'd probably make it there

582
00:24:11,920 --> 00:24:15,440
early-ish, like probably quarter two, 1130 quarter two.

583
00:24:15,440 --> 00:24:16,559
That seem fair?

584
00:24:16,559 --> 00:24:17,059
Sure.

585
00:24:17,840 --> 00:24:21,360
You stroll in and there's a, it's a very thin crowd

586
00:24:21,360 --> 00:24:25,120
compared to the scene that you walked into last night.

587
00:24:27,680 --> 00:24:30,559
There's one bartender who's kind of cleaning up,

588
00:24:31,440 --> 00:24:33,440
cleaning up the glasses and the tables

589
00:24:33,440 --> 00:24:37,360
and just rearranging after a night of frivolity

590
00:24:38,640 --> 00:24:40,160
that the city had underwent.

591
00:24:40,960 --> 00:24:43,680
Is there the bartender that was working yesterday in there?

592
00:24:43,680 --> 00:24:44,880
Is there a different one this time?

593
00:24:46,080 --> 00:24:47,920
There is a different one.

594
00:24:49,279 --> 00:24:49,840
Perfect.

595
00:24:49,840 --> 00:24:53,120
I'll stroll over to the bar and I'll say,

596
00:24:54,080 --> 00:24:56,559
Bartender, have you seen Gabriel?

597
00:24:56,559 --> 00:24:57,680
Has he been in yet?

598
00:24:57,680 --> 00:25:02,240
Gabriel, no.

599
00:25:02,240 --> 00:25:06,480
He usually gets in later.

600
00:25:07,519 --> 00:25:08,960
I'm supposed to meet him here at noon.

601
00:25:10,720 --> 00:25:17,440
Okay, well, hopefully he's keeping his appointments today.

602
00:25:19,039 --> 00:25:20,880
The way you said that makes it seem like maybe

603
00:25:20,880 --> 00:25:22,320
that's not what happens every day.

604
00:25:22,320 --> 00:25:23,759
Is that not what happens every day?

605
00:25:24,400 --> 00:25:26,080
You don't know Gabriel very well, do you?

606
00:25:26,720 --> 00:25:27,599
Uh, no, no.

607
00:25:28,960 --> 00:25:31,439
Okay, well, sometimes he does.

608
00:25:31,439 --> 00:25:32,639
Sometimes he's really good.

609
00:25:32,639 --> 00:25:36,159
Sometimes he's punctual and sometimes he's not.

610
00:25:37,359 --> 00:25:41,759
So, okay, so just, I'll get, I'll get what I get, I guess, huh?

611
00:25:41,759 --> 00:25:42,799
That's what I'm getting at.

612
00:25:43,439 --> 00:25:44,720
Can I get you anything while you wait?

613
00:25:45,679 --> 00:25:50,000
Do you have any, like, decks of cards or anything

614
00:25:50,000 --> 00:25:53,359
I can maybe borrow or kill some time before he shows up?

615
00:25:53,360 --> 00:25:55,760
He kind of looks around.

616
00:25:56,480 --> 00:25:57,920
I think we used to have something here.

617
00:25:59,520 --> 00:26:02,880
He lifts up a bunch of stuff underneath one of the tables

618
00:26:02,880 --> 00:26:06,320
or behind the bar and then pulls out a deck of cards

619
00:26:06,320 --> 00:26:07,520
and tosses it across to you.

620
00:26:07,520 --> 00:26:08,960
So yeah, there you go.

621
00:26:11,120 --> 00:26:12,160
I'll just go.

622
00:26:12,160 --> 00:26:13,120
Nothing to eat or drink?

623
00:26:14,080 --> 00:26:17,520
Yeah, do you have something like a lighter beer?

624
00:26:17,520 --> 00:26:18,640
Something in that neighborhood?

625
00:26:18,640 --> 00:26:20,960
It's a little early for me to start with the heavy stuff.

626
00:26:21,520 --> 00:26:22,480
I mean, we got water.

627
00:26:23,360 --> 00:26:24,560
I'll take one of those, sure.

628
00:26:27,840 --> 00:26:30,240
What's the lightest beer you have?

629
00:26:30,240 --> 00:26:30,720
Water.

630
00:26:30,720 --> 00:26:34,240
Some places do not look kindly on those who order just water.

631
00:26:34,240 --> 00:26:35,120
That's fair.

632
00:26:35,120 --> 00:26:38,480
You seem like a nice kid and you're going to be waiting on Gabriel a while.

633
00:26:38,480 --> 00:26:40,080
I'm not going to steal your money.

634
00:26:40,080 --> 00:26:41,200
I'll give you some water.

635
00:26:42,160 --> 00:26:44,640
He slides a glass across the bar to you.

636
00:26:45,760 --> 00:26:46,640
Perfect, yeah, thanks.

637
00:26:46,640 --> 00:26:48,080
I'll just, I'll be over there.

638
00:26:48,080 --> 00:26:49,440
If you see Gabriel, send him my way.

639
00:26:49,440 --> 00:26:54,880
I'm sure you'll see him before anybody else does.

640
00:26:54,880 --> 00:26:58,320
Well, I'm just going to be looking at the door nonstop, so yes, probably.

641
00:26:58,880 --> 00:27:02,160
If he sneaks in through the back way, there's no back way.

642
00:27:03,600 --> 00:27:04,640
Just keep an eye out.

643
00:27:04,640 --> 00:27:05,360
Perfect, will do.

644
00:27:05,360 --> 00:27:07,840
He goes back to shining up the glasses there.

645
00:27:07,840 --> 00:27:09,360
So you sit down at one of the tables

646
00:27:10,559 --> 00:27:14,640
and you hear some footsteps coming down the stairs

647
00:27:14,640 --> 00:27:18,799
and you see the dragonborn that you saw last night as Glim enters the room.

648
00:27:19,440 --> 00:27:20,400
Glim, what do you do?

649
00:27:20,400 --> 00:27:22,880
I mean, I was just making the stupidest big smile

650
00:27:22,880 --> 00:27:28,480
and that's probably, was actually, I, Carla, was doing it.

651
00:27:28,480 --> 00:27:30,880
But really, it's probably what Glim would do too

652
00:27:30,880 --> 00:27:32,320
because she would recognize him.

653
00:27:32,320 --> 00:27:33,200
She'd be excited.

654
00:27:34,799 --> 00:27:37,440
So I'm going to walk down the stairs and...

655
00:27:38,799 --> 00:27:39,600
Tell him you love him.

656
00:27:40,640 --> 00:27:41,519
Not yet.

657
00:27:41,519 --> 00:27:42,720
I barely know him.

658
00:27:42,720 --> 00:27:43,680
I just really like him.

659
00:27:43,680 --> 00:27:45,279
We did not ride on a caravan together for days on end.

660
00:27:45,279 --> 00:27:46,880
I really like him quite a bit.

661
00:27:47,440 --> 00:27:48,400
He was so clumsy.

662
00:27:50,000 --> 00:27:50,960
What's falling down?

663
00:27:51,920 --> 00:27:53,360
So yeah, I'm going to walk up and say,

664
00:27:54,400 --> 00:27:55,360
good morning.

665
00:27:55,360 --> 00:27:57,840
Oh, oh, it's you again.

666
00:27:57,840 --> 00:27:58,000
Hi.

667
00:27:58,000 --> 00:27:59,039
It's you again.

668
00:27:59,039 --> 00:27:59,680
How are you?

669
00:28:00,400 --> 00:28:01,680
I'm great.

670
00:28:01,680 --> 00:28:03,759
I had a great night's sleep last night.

671
00:28:03,759 --> 00:28:08,000
I'm excited for, I guess it's my first day of school to an extent.

672
00:28:08,640 --> 00:28:10,559
Oh, that's an exciting day.

673
00:28:10,559 --> 00:28:12,480
I can't remember if I gave you my name.

674
00:28:12,480 --> 00:28:14,559
I'm Glim and I hold my hand out.

675
00:28:15,600 --> 00:28:17,360
Yeah, yeah, Glim, it's Moot.

676
00:28:18,000 --> 00:28:20,160
Moot, it is so great to see you again.

677
00:28:20,160 --> 00:28:21,680
Where are you going to go to school?

678
00:28:21,680 --> 00:28:23,120
What are you going to go to school for?

679
00:28:23,120 --> 00:28:24,000
Tell me everything.

680
00:28:24,800 --> 00:28:28,400
Okay, to answer the first question, I think it's here.

681
00:28:29,600 --> 00:28:31,440
Is it like a bartending school?

682
00:28:31,440 --> 00:28:32,640
No, no.

683
00:28:32,640 --> 00:28:34,000
Second question will cover that.

684
00:28:34,640 --> 00:28:38,080
I'm trying to learn magic.

685
00:28:39,440 --> 00:28:39,920
Oh.

686
00:28:39,920 --> 00:28:43,840
There was a guy here last night that the school,

687
00:28:43,840 --> 00:28:46,960
the Nogwood School of Wizcraft and Witchery

688
00:28:46,960 --> 00:28:50,000
sent me over here to talk to this Gabriel fellow.

689
00:28:50,000 --> 00:28:52,000
So I'm hoping he'll be able to help me out.

690
00:28:52,559 --> 00:28:53,440
What kind of magic?

691
00:28:53,440 --> 00:28:54,319
I see you've got cards.

692
00:28:54,319 --> 00:28:56,720
Are you going to do like card tricks?

693
00:28:56,720 --> 00:28:57,600
Sleight of hand?

694
00:28:57,600 --> 00:28:59,680
What kind of magic are you going to learn?

695
00:28:59,680 --> 00:29:00,480
If only.

696
00:29:00,480 --> 00:29:03,120
We had a magician, quote unquote,

697
00:29:03,120 --> 00:29:07,279
that came to our village one time and he was really good with that stuff.

698
00:29:07,279 --> 00:29:09,440
But he wouldn't tell me how any of them were done.

699
00:29:09,440 --> 00:29:11,360
I love a magician.

700
00:29:11,360 --> 00:29:15,120
I guess it's in their code or something that they don't want to tell you.

701
00:29:15,120 --> 00:29:18,080
I asked so many questions and they wouldn't tell me any of the secrets.

702
00:29:18,080 --> 00:29:19,760
Yeah, it's the worst.

703
00:29:19,760 --> 00:29:24,000
But no, so I don't think it's going to be that type of magic.

704
00:29:25,280 --> 00:29:31,200
I seem to have what the lady at the school called was wild magic.

705
00:29:31,200 --> 00:29:35,280
Oh, that sounds exciting and kind of dangerous.

706
00:29:35,280 --> 00:29:36,240
Is it dangerous?

707
00:29:36,240 --> 00:29:37,040
It was scary.

708
00:29:37,600 --> 00:29:40,080
Yeah, I can't really control it.

709
00:29:40,080 --> 00:29:42,320
So I'm hoping that's what Gabriel can help me out with.

710
00:29:43,279 --> 00:29:43,759
Wow.

711
00:29:43,759 --> 00:29:44,240
You know what?

712
00:29:44,240 --> 00:29:48,559
It sounds like we have a lot in common because I also have a very special gift.

713
00:29:49,279 --> 00:29:49,679
Really?

714
00:29:51,200 --> 00:29:54,879
I'm like, I mean, this sounds conceited,

715
00:29:54,879 --> 00:29:57,359
but I think I'm like maybe going to help save the world.

716
00:29:58,799 --> 00:29:59,599
I have a calling.

717
00:30:00,559 --> 00:30:00,879
Wow.

718
00:30:01,519 --> 00:30:04,960
Yeah, I mean, no, I shot like this freezing ray out of my hands one time.

719
00:30:04,960 --> 00:30:06,159
Yours is way cooler.

720
00:30:06,159 --> 00:30:07,039
I don't know if it is.

721
00:30:07,039 --> 00:30:09,200
A freezing ray sounds pretty cool.

722
00:30:09,200 --> 00:30:11,439
But like saving the world, that's awesome.

723
00:30:11,440 --> 00:30:14,240
Well, I mean, if I'm going to be honest, and we're friends now,

724
00:30:14,240 --> 00:30:21,279
so I feel like I can be honest, I don't exactly know how I'm going to do that.

725
00:30:22,320 --> 00:30:22,960
Okay.

726
00:30:22,960 --> 00:30:25,279
But I think that I can.

727
00:30:25,279 --> 00:30:31,759
I'm looking for, hey, I'm looking for some people to help me.

728
00:30:32,400 --> 00:30:32,640
And I...

729
00:30:33,600 --> 00:30:34,960
To help you save the world?

730
00:30:34,960 --> 00:30:39,680
This sounds kind of crazy, but I think you might be one of them.

731
00:30:41,519 --> 00:30:42,720
What makes you say that?

732
00:30:42,720 --> 00:30:47,440
I'm like, I don't even know how to do this magic stuff.

733
00:30:47,440 --> 00:30:49,039
I just have a feeling.

734
00:30:49,039 --> 00:30:49,759
I don't know.

735
00:30:49,759 --> 00:30:50,559
I don't know, Moot.

736
00:30:50,559 --> 00:30:52,080
I just have a feeling about you.

737
00:30:53,279 --> 00:30:54,559
Okay, that's cool.

738
00:30:55,120 --> 00:31:01,279
The door opens with a loud bang and then heavy footsteps and Moot,

739
00:31:01,279 --> 00:31:07,039
you see Gabriel kind of, he's got a hat that's low on his face.

740
00:31:07,600 --> 00:31:08,480
Sunglasses are on.

741
00:31:09,120 --> 00:31:10,400
Tucked into himself.

742
00:31:11,039 --> 00:31:14,960
And he goes over and up to the bar and just holds up a finger

743
00:31:14,960 --> 00:31:19,519
and the bartender slides him a drink as he kind of just sits there for a moment

744
00:31:20,319 --> 00:31:22,160
while you're still conversing.

745
00:31:22,720 --> 00:31:25,360
Have I noticed Gabriel come in or am I...?

746
00:31:25,360 --> 00:31:30,000
Yeah, I mean, I figure you've kind of got at least half an eye on the door

747
00:31:30,000 --> 00:31:32,000
the whole time even while you're talking with Glim.

748
00:31:32,720 --> 00:31:34,400
So yeah, you definitely see him.

749
00:31:34,400 --> 00:31:38,880
I kind of excitedly tap Glim on the hand.

750
00:31:39,600 --> 00:31:40,400
I say, oh, that's him.

751
00:31:40,400 --> 00:31:41,040
That's Gabriel.

752
00:31:42,000 --> 00:31:43,200
That's the guy who's going to teach me.

753
00:31:44,480 --> 00:31:45,040
That guy.

754
00:31:46,240 --> 00:31:48,480
Yeah, that's who the school told me to find.

755
00:31:49,120 --> 00:31:51,600
Glim, you definitely see someone who is...

756
00:31:52,240 --> 00:31:52,720
He looks pretty rough.

757
00:31:52,720 --> 00:31:55,040
If not half in the bag, he's rough.

758
00:31:55,040 --> 00:31:58,320
He's probably still drunk and hungover at the same time.

759
00:31:58,320 --> 00:32:00,240
Yeah, like I can probably smell him.

760
00:32:00,960 --> 00:32:02,800
Oh, yeah, there's an odor.

761
00:32:02,800 --> 00:32:03,519
Roll for smell.

762
00:32:04,640 --> 00:32:05,519
Roll for odor.

763
00:32:06,560 --> 00:32:07,200
It's a good one.

764
00:32:07,200 --> 00:32:07,759
Yeah.

765
00:32:07,759 --> 00:32:08,400
Yeah.

766
00:32:08,400 --> 00:32:09,200
Pungent.

767
00:32:09,200 --> 00:32:09,700
Yeah.

768
00:32:10,480 --> 00:32:11,040
Huh.

769
00:32:11,040 --> 00:32:14,560
Well, and he's a teacher?

770
00:32:15,840 --> 00:32:20,400
Well, I guess he studied wild magic at the school

771
00:32:20,400 --> 00:32:24,480
because he thought there was something that he could tap into with it.

772
00:32:24,480 --> 00:32:26,960
But I guess they kind of also kicked him out of the school for...

773
00:32:28,080 --> 00:32:29,920
I mean, the lady at the school said

774
00:32:29,920 --> 00:32:33,840
she didn't say he wasted his time, but I think that's kind of what she felt.

775
00:32:35,360 --> 00:32:36,160
Hmm.

776
00:32:36,160 --> 00:32:43,360
Well, you can't judge a magician by their smell, I always say.

777
00:32:44,400 --> 00:32:48,320
So I guess I should leave you to school.

778
00:32:49,200 --> 00:32:50,560
It was really good to see you again.

779
00:32:50,560 --> 00:32:51,200
Are you going to...

780
00:32:51,200 --> 00:32:52,240
Maybe I'll see you back here.

781
00:32:52,240 --> 00:32:53,360
I'm staying here.

782
00:32:53,360 --> 00:32:54,400
Oh, you're staying here?

783
00:32:54,400 --> 00:32:54,640
Cool.

784
00:32:54,640 --> 00:32:55,440
I'm staying here.

785
00:32:55,440 --> 00:32:56,560
I'm just over at the school,

786
00:32:56,560 --> 00:33:00,560
but I imagine because I think this is like Gabriel's base of operations.

787
00:33:00,560 --> 00:33:02,000
I think we're going to be here a while.

788
00:33:02,720 --> 00:33:03,119
Okay.

789
00:33:03,119 --> 00:33:07,839
Well, I'm going to, you know, go about my day, but you're my friend now.

790
00:33:07,839 --> 00:33:09,359
I'm going to see you again, Moot.

791
00:33:09,359 --> 00:33:10,799
Good luck with school.

792
00:33:10,799 --> 00:33:12,559
